                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN MARS</hi> (35)</persName>
                  <rs id="t18771022-758-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18771022-758-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18771022-758-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp>, Feloniously cutting and wounding <persName id="t18771022-name-68" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-68" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-68" type="surname" value="DAELMANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-68" type="given" value="ALBERT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-68" type="occupation" value="seaman- second mate"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18771022-758-offence-1 t18771022-name-68"></join>Albert Daelmans</persName>, with intent to do him some grievous bodily harm.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DENISON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-69" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-69" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-69" type="surname" value="DAELMANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-69" type="given" value="ALBERT"></interp>ALBERT DAELMANS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am second mate of the Baron Osy—I was on on board on Saturday, 29th September—the prisoner was employed as stevedore—the ship was lying off Iron Gate Wharf—I gave the prisoner instructions; he told me to shut up—I told Mr. Nye, my employer—the prisoner then knocked me with this hook in the face, and hit me in the eye and on the nose—I fell down—a man laid hold of him and he was detained.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by the Prisoner.</hi> I did not get hold of you by this hook, nor by a small hook, nor punch you with my fist, nor knock you down.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-70" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-70" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-70" type="surname" value="NYE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-70" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS NYE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a stevedore, of 5, Ada Road, Bow—on the evening of 29th September the last witness made a communication to me and I called the prisoner out of the hold—he came up with a small hook and dropped</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="187710220008"></xptr>
               <p>it and attacked Daelmans with a large hook—I said "You d—d mur<lb></lb>derer, what are you doing of; do you mean to kill the man?"—I got the hook from him; he was eat up with passion—he has worked for me six or seven years.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined.</hi> I got you down on the deck and hit you hard.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18771022-name-71" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-71" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-71" type="surname" value="PLUMMER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18771022-name-71" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD PLUMMER</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Thames Police Inspector</hi>). I was called to the Baron Osy on 29th September and saw the prosecutor bleeding from a slight wound under his right eye and on his nose—he told me in the prisoner's presence that the prisoner had assaulted him—I took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">PRISONER'S DEFENCE</hi>. This mate told me I was not working hard enough—I said I could not work harder—he asked me a second and a third time—I told him to shut up, and he told Mr. Nye, who called me up, and then this mate snatched the hook and tore my jacket, which saved my flesh, and I thought it was time to defend myself—I closed with him and Mr. Nye came to his assistance—they got me down and thumped me, and called another man, who also tumbled on me—my teeth are loose now—the hook accidentally caught the mate in the face—I did not intend to hurt him, and he did not know he was hurt till somebody told him he was scratched—I have worked for him twelve years, and never had a quarrel before.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18771022-758-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18771022-758-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18771022-758-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="lesserOffence"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>
                     <hi rend="italic">of unlawfully wounding. Recommended to mercy by the Jury—</hi>
                  </rs>
                  <hi rend="italic">
                     <rs id="t18771022-758-punishment-9" type="punishmentDescription">
